{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-12-13","name":"William Fossard","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"William Fossard","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"William"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"Fossard"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"William of Mulgrave","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1115–1167","fullLifespan":"Abt 1115–after 1167","birthDate":"+1115","birthPlace":{"address":"Yorkshire, England","geo":{"latitude":53.95878,"longitude":-1.08248,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1167","userCertifiedLifeSummary":"«b»Biography«/b»\nIn 1138, William was involved in the battle of the Standard against David, King of Scots. The chronicle of Richard of Hexham records that before the battle William was among those Yorkshire barons who assembled with Archbishop Thurstan at York to debate the best course of action to be taken in response to David's aggressive activities in northern England.\n\nWilliam was still supporting King Stephen's cause in 1141 when he was captured at the battle of Lincoln.\n\nHe made a donation to Watton Priory between 1154 and 1160, which referred to his impending journey to Jerusalem, and he may have been on crusade during the early years of Henry II's reign. It was probably this William who made a grant to the Hospitallers of Jerusalem at Huntington near York and he was a generous patron of a number of East Riding religious houses including Meaux, Ellerton, and Swine.\n\nIn 1166 the return of Hugh, bishop of Durham, recorded that William held one knight's fee from the bishop in the East Riding and his own return listed thirty-three and a half fees of the old and new enfeoffment.\n\nIn 1169, the custody of his son William was given by Henry II to William le Gros.","sourceList":[{"title":"Book - Early Yorkshire Charters  Vol 6","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceUri":"SJ5M-V5G"},{"title":"Burke's Peerage","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceUri":"9P1C-XVV"},{"title":"Yorkshire: An Historical and Topographical Introduction to a Knowledge of ... By John Wainwright","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://books.google.com/books?id=LkIIAAAAQAAJ&q=william+fossard#v=snippet&q=william%20fossard&f=false","sourceUri":"9NGS-LZT"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1115","date":"Abt 1115","place":"Yorkshire, England"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1135","date":"1135","place":"Mulgrave Castle, Yorkshire, England","age":"20","id":"MFCZ-7CT"},{"name":"Death","sources":"0","year":"1167","date":"after 1167","age":"53"},{"name":"Marriage","sources":"0","type":"Spousal","id":"G2KM-P9R"}],"parent":[{"name":"Robert Fossard I","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1079–1135","birthDate":"+1079","deathDate":"+1135","age":56,"@type":"Person","identifier":"MFCZ-7CT","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/MFCZ-7CT/robert-fossard-i-1079-1135","published":true}],"sibling":[{"name":"Emma Fossard","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1100–1164","birthDate":"A+1100","deathDate":"+1164","age":64,"@type":"Person","identifier":"LDBQ-PQQ","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/LDBQ-PQQ/emma-fossard-1100-1164","published":true},{"name":"Aufrida Fossard","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1110–1145","birthDate":"A+1110","deathDate":"+1145","age":35,"@type":"Person","identifier":"94KN-GFW","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/94KN-GFW/aufrida-fossard-1110-1145","published":true},{"name":"Geoffrey Fossard","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1114–1166","birthDate":"+1114","deathDate":"+1166/","age":53,"@type":"Person","identifier":"L8RR-4ZV","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/L8RR-4ZV/geoffrey-fossard-1114-1166","published":true},{"name":"Agnes Fossard","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1115–1153","birthDate":"+1115","deathDate":"+1153","age":38,"@type":"Person","identifier":"L8RR-4Z8","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/L8RR-4Z8/agnes-fossard-1115-1153","published":true},{"name":"William Fossard","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1115–1167","birth